{
  "texts": [
    "Our approach is motivated by the observation that DPO inherently learns token-level rewards.",
    "Instead of directly optimizing the policy model with auto-labeled token-level rewards, T-REG retains sequence-level preference optimization while using these token-level rewards as weak supervision.",
    "This weak supervision regularizes the token-level reward signals implicitly learned during preference optimization.",
    "This design enables T-REG to optimize the overall sequence-level reward while also achieving effective token-level credit assignment.",
    "Inspired by the self-refinement capabilities of LLMs (Madaan et al., 2024), we derive tokenlevel rewards through contrastive prompting, where revision-based prompts rewrite the output in opposing directions."
  ]
}